burnTokensOf(address,uint256,uint256,str.details: Only a token's holder, a designated operator, or a project's terminal can burn it.

params._holder: The account that is having its tokens burned.
params._memo: A memo to pass along to the emitted event.
params._preferClaimedTokens: A flag indicating whether a project's attached token contract should be burned first if they have been issued.
params._projectId: The ID of the project to which the tokens being burned belong.
params._tokenCount: The number of tokens to burn.

params._directory: A contract storing directories of terminals and controllers for each project.
params._fundingCycleStore: A contract storing all funding cycle configurations.
params._projects: A contract which mints ERC-721's that represent project ownership and transfers.
params._splitsStore: A contract that stores splits for each project.
params._tokenStore: A contract that manages token minting and burning.

params._projectId: The ID of the project to which the funding cycle belongs.

params._memo: A memo to pass along to the emitted event.
params._projectId: The ID of the project to which the reserved tokens belong.

returns._0: The amount of minted reserved tokens.

distributionLimitOf(uint256,uint256,addr.details: The number of decimals in the returned fixed point amount is the same as that of the specified terminal.

params._configuration: The configuration during which the distribution limit applies.
params._projectId: The ID of the project to get the distribution limit of.
params._terminal: The terminal from which distributions are being limited.
params._token: The token for which the distribution limit applies.

returns._0: The distribution limit, as a fixed point number with the same number of decimals as the provided terminal.
returns._1: The currency of the distribution limit.

The ID of the project to which the funding cycle belongs.

launchFundingCyclesFor(uint256,(uint256,.details: Each operation within this transaction can be done in sequence separately.Only a project owner or operator can launch its funding cycles.

params._data: Data that defines the project's first funding cycle. These properties will remain fixed for the duration of the funding cycle.
params._fundAccessConstraints: An array containing amounts that a project can use from its treasury for each payment terminal. Amounts are fixed point numbers using the same number of decimals as the accompanying terminal. The `_distributionLimit` and `_overflowAllowance` parameters must fit in a `uint232`.
params._groupedSplits: An array of splits to set for any number of groups.
params._memo: A memo to pass along to the emitted event.
params._metadata: Metadata specifying the controller specific params that a funding cycle can have. These properties will remain fixed for the duration of the funding cycle.
params._mustStartAtOrAfter: The time before which the configured funding cycle cannot start.
params._projectId: The ID of the project to launch funding cycles for.
params._terminals: Payment terminals to add for the project.

returns.configuration: The configuration of the funding cycle that was successfully created.

launchProjectFor(address,(string,uint256.details: Each operation within this transaction can be done in sequence separately.Anyone can deploy a project on an owner's behalf.

params._data: Data that defines the project's first funding cycle. These properties will remain fixed for the duration of the funding cycle.
params._fundAccessConstraints: An array containing amounts that a project can use from its treasury for each payment terminal. Amounts are fixed point numbers using the same number of decimals as the accompanying terminal. The `_distributionLimit` and `_overflowAllowance` parameters must fit in a `uint232`.
params._groupedSplits: An array of splits to set for any number of groups.
params._memo: A memo to pass along to the emitted event.
params._metadata: Metadata specifying the controller specific params that a funding cycle can have. These properties will remain fixed for the duration of the funding cycle.
params._mustStartAtOrAfter: The time before which the configured funding cycle cannot start.
params._owner: The address to set as the owner of the project. The project ERC-721 will be owned by this address.
params._projectMetadata: Metadata to associate with the project within a particular domain. This can be updated any time by the owner of the project.
params._terminals: Payment terminals to add for the project.

migrate(uint256,address).details: Only a project's owner or a designated operator can migrate it.

params._projectId: The ID of the project that will be migrated from this controller.
params._to: The controller to which the project is migrating.

mintTokensOf(uint256,uint256,address,str.details: Only a project's owner, a designated operator, one of its terminals, or the current data source can mint its tokens.

params._beneficiary: The account that the tokens are being minted for.
params._memo: A memo to pass along to the emitted event.
params._preferClaimedTokens: A flag indicating whether a project's attached token contract should be minted if they have been issued.
params._projectId: The ID of the project to which the tokens being minted belong.
params._tokenCount: The amount of tokens to mint in total, counting however many should be reserved.
params._useReservedRate: Whether to use the current funding cycle's reserved rate in the mint calculation.

returns.beneficiaryTokenCount: The amount of tokens minted for the beneficiary.

overflowAllowanceOf(uint256,uint256,addr.details: The number of decimals in the returned fixed point amount is the same as that of the specified terminal.

params._configuration: The configuration of the during which the allowance applies.
params._projectId: The ID of the project to get the overflow allowance of.
params._token: The token for which the overflow allowance applies.

returns._0: The overflow allowance, as a fixed point number with the same number of decimals as the provided terminal.
returns._1: The currency of the overflow allowance.
